            <div class="text-[#3A403A] space-y-5">
                <p class="text-xl font-bold border-l-4 border-[#82998A] pl-3">
                    Project Summary: Probabilistic Decision Making
                </p>
                <p>
                    **Quantum Chess** is a conceptual board game developed in C++ to simulate complex game theory decisions where pieces can exist in multiple states simultaneously (superposition) until a move "observations" their true position.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The challenge lay in designing the AI opponent. It utilizes a modified **Minimax algorithm** which had to be rewritten to account for the multiple simultaneous, probabilistic outcomes of each move. This expanded the traditional decision tree exponentially, forcing an emphasis on efficient pruning and state evaluation, demonstrating an advanced grasp of algorithmic optimization.
                </p>
                
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold pt-4 text-[#82998A]">Key Technologies & Skills Demonstrated</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2 text-lg">
                    <li>**Language:** C++ üöÄ (Chosen for performance and low-level control)</li>
                    <li>**Library:** SFML (Used for window management and graphics rendering).</li>
                    <li>**AI:** Modified Minimax algorithm for probabilistic outcomes and efficient tree pruning.</li>
                    <li>**Concept:** Implementation of complex probabilistic state management.</li>
                </ul>

